✅ Default Constructor
A constructor that takes no parameters.
It is called automatically when an object is created.
If no constructor is written, C# provides a default constructor by default.
✅ Parameterized Constructor
A constructor that takes arguments (parameters).
Used to initialize an object with specific values.
✅ Copy Constructor
A constructor that creates a new object by copying another object.
It takes an object of the same class as a parameter.
✅ Private Constructor
A constructor that is private and cannot be accessed from outside the class.
Used to restrict object creation.
